spans.text: a Steed that felt its smarting Wound
the Ground : At length , proud Israel began to fail , Our juster Cause
through the Wood their mighty Numbers fly

raged our General through the dreadful Gloom , Pale Terror hovered on his waving Plume ; From his known Spear the shrieking Numbers run , And from his Fury fled your conquered Son ; Grim Danger urged him on with fatal Speed , And through black Shades he lashed the weary Steed : In the dark Centre of this Forest stood A lofty Oak , which overlooked the Wood
from his Fury fled your conquered Son
the dark Centre of this Forest

a Grove of Spears : Now , Traitor , fall — our mighty Leader cries : ( While glowing Vengeance sparkled in his Eyes ) Then stepped a Captain of the loyal Band , And vainly strove to stay his fatal Hand
glowing Vengeance sparkled in his Eyes
glowing Vengeance sparkled in his Eyes
with a Groan the beauteous Rebel died
the weeping King , Thy horrid Tale
O Absalom — O Absalom , my Son , Eternal Shade has sealed thy cheerful Eyes
milder Songs attend his noontide Ray
